{{Infobox comic book title |image = Jersey Gods 12 cover.jpg |imagesize = |caption = |schedule = |limited = |Fantasy = |publisher = Image Comics |startmo = February |startyr = 2009 |endmo = May |endyr = 2010 |issues = 12 |main_char_team = |writers = Glen Brunswick |artists = Dan McDaid |pencillers = |inkers = |letterers = |colorists = Rachelle Rosenberg |editors = |creative_team_month = |creative_team_year = |creators = |TPB = |ISBN = |TPB# = |ISBN# = |subcat = |altcat = |sort = Jersey Gods |addpubcat# = }} '''''Jersey Gods''''' is a [[comic book]] published by [[Image Comics]]. It was written by [[Glen Brunswick]], pencilled and inked by [[Dan McDaid]], with colors by [[Rachelle Rosenberg]]. The covers were drawn by [[Mike Allred]] and coloured by [[Laura Allred]].<ref>http://www.comicbookresources.com/?page=article&id=20997</ref> Alternative covers were also provided by [[Dan McDaid]], [[Darwyn Cooke]], [[Paul Pope]] and [[Whilce Porticio]]. A back-up strip, ''Tales from the Great War'', was written by [[Mark Waid]] and drawn by [[Joe Infurnari]].<ref>http://www.comicbookresources.com/?page=article&id=20576</ref> Prior to publication, teaser strips appeared in ''[[Popgun (comics)|Popgun]] volume 2'' and ''[[Invincible (comics)|Invincible]] 55''.
==Plot== The central story concerns the romantic relationship between Zoe, an ordinary resident of New Jersey, and Barock, a God from the fictional world of Neboron.
